T1  - Lotsizing and Scheduling on Parallel Machines with Sequence-Dependent Setup Costs
AU  - Kang, Sungmin
AU  - Malik, Kavindra
AU  - Thomas, L. Joseph
Y1  - 1999/02/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.45.2.273
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.45.2.273
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 273
EP  - 289
VL  - 45
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Industrial lotsizing and scheduling pose very difficult analytical problems. We propose an unconventional model that deals with sequence-dependent setup costs in a multiple-machine environment. The sequence-splitting model splits an entire schedule into subsequences, leading to tractable subproblems. An optimization approach based on a column generation/branch and bound methodology is developed, and heuristically adapted to test problems including five real-world problem instances gathered from industry.
AB  - Industrial lotsizing and scheduling pose very difficult analytical problems. We propose an unconventional model that deals with sequence-dependent setup costs in a multiple-machine environment. The sequence-splitting model splits an entire schedule into subsequences, leading to tractable subproblems. An optimization approach based on a column generation/branch and bound methodology is developed, and heuristically adapted to test problems including five real-world problem instances gathered from industry.
